Lahore District (Urdu:  ) is a district in the Punjab province of Pakistan that contains the city of Lahore, the district and provincial capital. The total area is 1,772 square kilometres (684sqmi). According to the 1998 census, the population was 6,318,745, of which 81.17% were urban.[1] Until the local government reforms of 2000, Lahore was part of the now-defunct Lahore Division. With the revival of commissioner system division, Lahore was restored. Under the latest revision of Pakistan's administrative structure, promulgated in 2001,[2] Lahore was tagged as a City District and divided into nine towns.[3] Each town in turn consists of a group of union councils.[4] Coordinates: 3125N 7420E / 31.417N 74.333E / 31.417; 74.333
